==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carob
<hw>Car"ob</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>caroube</ets> fruit of the carob tree, Sp. <ets>garrobo</ets>,
<ets>al-garrobo</ets>, carob tree, fr. Ar. <ets>kharr⟦umac⟧b</ets>, Per.
<ets>Kharn⟦umac⟧b</ets>. Cf. <er>Clgaroba</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An evergreen leguminous tree (<spn>Ceratania
Siliqua</spn>) found in the countries bordering the Mediterranean; the
St. John's bread; -- called also <altname>carob
tree</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the long, sweet, succulent, pods of the carob
tree, which are used as food for animals and sometimes eaten by man; --
called also <altname>St. John's bread</altname>, <altname>carob
bean</altname>, and <altname>algaroba bean</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caroche</ent>⟦br⟧
